      "name":"Filipi Pires","image":"https://sessionize.com/image/ce80-400o400o2-7RzGhiAL2PpoCHfT3sQZXs.jpg","href": "https://twitter.com/FilipiPires",
      "bio":"I’ve been working as Security and Threat Researcher at Saporo, Founder at Black&White Technology, Developer Advocate at TestKube, Cybersecurity Advocate at senhasegura, Snyk Ambassador, Application Security Specialist and Hacking is NOT a crime Advocate. International Speakers in Security and New technologies events in many countries such as US, Canada, France, Spain, Germany, Poland, and others, I’ve been served as University Professor in Graduation and MBA courses at Brazilian colleges, in addition, I'm Creator and Instructor of the Course Malware Attack Types with Kill Chain Methodology (PentestMagazine) and Malware Analysis - Fundamentals (HackerSec).",
      "talks": [
        {
          "title": "Adopting the GitOps testing model into your Kubernetes CI/CD workflow",
          "abstract": "One of the major trends in contemporary cloud native application development is the adoption of GitOps when it comes to infrastructure automation. Testing will also be following this trend as the industry is getting more aware of the advantages of having tests be part of the state of application’s cluster. In this talk, we will discuss what those advantages are and how attendees can improve how testing is done on applications throughout their organization.\r\n\r\nLet’s have a look at TestKube, an open-source framework that aims to move cloud-native testing into Kubernetes. Whether you are using Postman, Cypress, JMeter, Selenium, or any other testing tool, TestKube will decouple your test execution pipeline from constraints specific to CI/CD tools and allow you to repurpose existing tests using a Kubernetes native approach to test orchestration, execution and test result management.",
          "format": "Presentation (40m)",
          "level": "Intermediate"
        }
      ]
